beta\", followed by the literal domain and path. I'll use this approach for the implementation. url(url):\n    pattern = r'(www|beta)\\.example\\.com/$'\n    return bool(re.fullmatch(pattern, url))\n```\n\nBoth approaches work—`re.fullmatch()` returns a Match object or None, and wrapping it with `bool()` converts that to True or False. I could also use `is not None` for clarity, but the `bool()` conversion is more concise. I'll go with that simpler version.\n\nFor the implementation, a function seems like the right approach given the task description. The pattern should correctly validate URLs like \"www.example.com/\" and \"beta.example.com/\" while rejecting variations without the trailing slash or with additional paths.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4628,"cache_read_input_tokens":24095,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4628},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"79b9b6fa-2a5f-4de0-8ea5-940bf3faece5","uuid":"545c679e-a405-4b40-8af5-c67f716544ee","request_id":"req_011CbdNWAoyz7JUMMX5Rm88p"}
